[[!meta title="Screenshot and screencast"]]

To take a screenshot or record a screencast:

1. To start the camera widget, either:

   - Press the **PrtScn** key of the keyboard.

   - Click on [[!img lib/camera-photo.png alt="Take Screenshot" class="symbolic"
     link="no"]] in the system menu.

     [[!img first_steps/desktop/system-with-wifi-only.png link="no" class="screenshot" alt=""]]

1. The camera widget appears at the bottom of the screen.

   [[!img camera.png link="no" class="screenshot" alt=""]]

   - To turn on the screenshot mode, click on the [[!img lib/camera-photo.png
     alt="Screenshot" class="symbolic" link="no"]] button.

   - To turn on the screencast mode, click on the [[!img lib/camera-web.png
     alt="Screencast" class="symbolic" link="no"]] button.

1. Click on the [[!img lib/media-record.png alt="Screencast" class="symbolic"
   link="no"]] button to take a screenshot or start recording a screencast.

   - Screenshots are saved in **Places**&nbsp;▸ **Pictures**.

   - Screencasts are saved in **Places**&nbsp;▸ **Videos**.

<div class="bug">

<p>Screencasts don't record sound. You can record ambient sound using
<i>[[Sound Recorder|sound_and_video]]</i>.</p>

</div>
